ygData.subject: RE: Enjoy the Veterans Day break (off topic)
ygData.msgSnippet: I ll look you up this weekend Galtin...Saturday 10am-7pm CST is my big game day since I too get to be home alone while my poor wife is working. Unfortunately,
ygData.messageBody:
I'll look you up this weekend Galtin...Saturday 10am-7pm CST is my big game
day since I too get to be home alone while my poor wife is working.
Unfortunately, since I work in the private sector I don't get veteran's day
off :-(


-Faras

> -----Original Message-----
> From: Reece, Tom - 25IDL G4 [mailto:g4mntofcr@...]
> Sent: Wednesday, November 10, 1999 7:59 PM
> To: eqbards@onelist.com
> Subject: [eqbards] Enjoy the Veterans Day break (off topic)
>
>
> From: "Reece, Tom - 25IDL G4" <g4mntofcr@...>
>
> Want to wish all you veterans out there a good Veterans Day
> weekend. I for one
> am looking forward to the break. Since I'm in the US Army,
> I'm off through
> Monday. Combine that with my wife having to work(evil grin)
> and that means I
> get to play EQ all day tomorrow and Friday. This will be the
> first time in a
> long time I get to play for more than two hours at a time.
> Just might get the
> chance to finally make 27th level and play around with the
> Charm song some.
> Already printed out the song analysis that John Kim posted a
> few weeks back so I
> have it to refer to. Got my song scroll already in my
> backpack and I'm even
> gonna go ahead and make my pet hotkeys now in anticipation of
> gaining that song.
>
>
> For you E'ci bards (Kitasi, Faras, Aloro, Laluni, et.al.),
> look me up if you are
> online. Maybe we can all get together and work on getting
> quest components for
> our armor. I'm getting tired of MM and was thinking about
> heading to Solusek.
> An enchanter friend who is 35th level has already agreed to
> help me fight giants
> in order to get some lambent stones as well.
>
> Take care
> Galtin of E'ci
